Here is the review.

---

## PR Review: ListItem Component (L03510)

### What's Good

- **BEM naming** is correct and consistent throughout.
- **Token usage** is solid -- `$space-3`, `$radius-md`, `$transition-fast`, `$font-md`, `$font-sm`, `$font-xs`, `$color-text-secondary`, `$color-text-tertiary`, `$color-accent`, `$color-surface-hover` are all used appropriately.
- **Text truncation** on title and subtitle is properly handled with `white-space: nowrap; overflow: hidden; text-overflow: ellipsis`.
- **Icon sizing** matches spec (20x20) with `flex-shrink: 0`.
- **Height, padding, radius, cursor, transition** all match spec.
- **Empty accessories** guard (`accessories && accessories.length > 0`) is correct.
- **Missing icon** is handled (`icon &&`).
- **Integration** with `useListContext` and `data-list-index` for scroll-into-view is correct.
- **`role="option"` and `aria-selected`** on the item are correct given the parent `role="listbox"`.

---

### Issues That Must Be Fixed

#### 1. CRITICAL -- Hardcoded colors in active state (`list_item.scss` lines 22-34)

```scss
.list-item__title {
  color: #fff;
}
.list-item__subtitle {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
}
.list-item__icon {
  color: #fff;
}
.list-item__accessory-text {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
}
```

These are hardcoded magic values. The project mandates "Sass variables for all design tokens." The `#fff` and `rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7)` should be defined as tokens in `_tokens.scss` (e.g., `$color-text-on-accent` and `$color-text-on-accent-secondary`). This is not a pedantic point -- if the accent color ever changes to a light color, or if a light theme is added, these hardcoded whites will break.

**Fix**: Add to `_tokens.scss`:
```scss
$color-text-on-accent: #ffffff;
$color-text-on-accent-secondary: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7);
```
Then use them in `list_item.scss`.

#### 2. CRITICAL -- `ListItemAccessory` interface is not exported (`list_item.tsx` line 5)

```typescript
interface ListItemAccessory {
  text?: string;
  icon?: ReactNode;
}
```

Any consumer building a list needs to type their accessory data. Without the export, consumers must either inline the shape or use `as any` -- both are bad. `ListItemProps` should also be exported so consumers can spread or compose.

**Fix**: Export both interfaces and re-export from `index.ts`:
```typescript
export interface ListItemAccessory { ... }
export interface ListItemProps { ... }
```
```typescript
// index.ts
export { ListItem } from './list_item/list_item';
export type { ListItemProps, ListItemAccessory } from './list_item/list_item';
```

#### 3. CRITICAL -- No Enter/Return key support

The spec says `onClick handler`. Raycast activates the selected item on Enter. The parent `List` component handles ArrowUp/ArrowDown but does NOT handle Enter. The `ListItem` has an `onClick` but there is no keyboard path to trigger it. A keyboard-driven command palette that can't activate items with Enter is broken.

**Fix**: Either in `List` (preferred, since it owns the keyboard listener) add Enter handling that fires `onClick` on the active item, or in `ListItem` add a `tabIndex={0}` with an `onKeyDown` handler. The cleaner approach is to lift an `onActivate` callback into the List or pass Enter handling through context. At minimum, the List's keydown handler needs to dispatch Enter to the active item.

#### 4. HIGH -- Accessory gap uses hardcoded `2px` (`list_item.scss` line 86)

```scss
.list-item__accessory {
  gap: 2px;
}
```

`2px` is not a design token. The smallest token is `$space-1: 4px`. Either use `$space-1` or define a new token if 2px is intentional.

#### 5. HIGH -- `useCallback` wrapping `onClick` is pointless (`list_item.tsx` lines 37-39)

```typescript
const handleClick = useCallback(() => {
  onClick?.();
}, [onClick]);
```

This creates a new closure every time `onClick` changes, which is the same as just passing `onClick` directly. The `useCallback` adds overhead for zero benefit. Since `onClick` is already the only thing called, just pass it to the div:

```typescript
onClick={onClick}
```

Or if you want the optional chaining safety (though React handles `undefined` onClick fine), just remove the `useCallback` wrapper and inline:

```tsx
onClick={() => onClick?.()}
```

But honestly, `onClick={onClick}` is the cleanest.

#### 6. MEDIUM -- `__title` has no `min-width: 0` for truncation to work in flex

The `__left` container correctly has `min-width: 0`, but `__title` itself is a flex child without `min-width: 0`. In a nested flex layout, the title text won't truncate properly in some cases because the flex item won't shrink below its content width.

**Fix**: Add `min-width: 0` to `.list-item__title`.

#### 7. MEDIUM -- Accessory icon in active state has no color override

The `&--active` block overrides `__icon` color but accessory icons (the `ReactNode` inside `__accessory`) have no color override. If an accessory has an SVG icon using `currentColor`, it will remain the default color while text turns white, creating an inconsistent look.

**Fix**: Add to the `&--active` block:
```scss
.list-item__accessory {
  color: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.7); // use the token once created
}
```

#### 8. LOW -- `key={i}` on accessories (`list_item.tsx` line 58)

Using array index as key is a React anti-pattern when the list can reorder. If accessories are always static per render, this is acceptable. But if there's any chance accessories could change order or be conditionally included between renders, this will cause incorrect reconciliation. Consider whether `ListItemAccessory` should have an `id` field.

This is low priority since accessories are typically static props, but worth noting.

---

### Summary

| # | Severity | Issue |
|---|----------|-------|
| 1 | CRITICAL | Hardcoded `#fff` / `rgba` colors -- need tokens |
| 2 | CRITICAL | `ListItemAccessory` and `ListItemProps` not exported |
| 3 | CRITICAL | No Enter key activation -- keyboard-only users can't activate items |
| 4 | HIGH | Hardcoded `2px` gap in accessory |
| 5 | HIGH | Pointless `useCallback` on `handleClick` |
| 6 | MEDIUM | Missing `min-width: 0` on `__title` for reliable truncation |
| 7 | MEDIUM | Accessory icon color not overridden in active state |
| 8 | LOW | Index-based key on accessories |

Issues 1-3 are blockers. The component cannot ship without exported types, tokenized colors, and Enter key support.
